Introduction into Machine Learning with Breast Cancer Dataset¶

The tasks in this project will go through doing the following:

  • Exploring the dataset
  • Feature Selection
  • Machine Learning
  • Deep Learning
In [1]:
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.datasets import load_breast_cancer

cancer = load_breast_cancer()

The object returned by load_breast_cancer() is a scikit-learn Bunch object, which is similar to a dictionary.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plotter
import seaborn as sns
In [10]:
def box_kde_plotter(x):
    sns.set(style="ticks")
    fig, (ax_box, ax_displot) = plotter.subplots(2, sharex=True, 
                                    gridspec_kw={"height_ratios": (.15, .85)})
    sns.boxplot(df[x], orient='horizontal', ax=ax_box)
    sns.histplot(df[x], ax=ax_displot, kde=True)  # Use histplot instead of displot
    ax_box.set(yticks=[])
    sns.despine(ax=ax_box, left=True)
for i in df.columns[:-1]:
    box_kde_plotter(i)
    plotter.show()

In [181]:
def sigmoid(x):
    return 1/(1 + np.exp(-x))
In [182]:
class Linear_Regression():
    def __init__(self,train_arr : np.array, y_arr : np.array, alpha=0.01):
        self.X = train_arr
        self.y = y_arr
        self.weights = np.zeros(self.X.shape[1])
        self.bias = 0
        self.alpha = alpha
    def fit(self,iterations : int):
        for _ in range(iterations):
            predictions = sigmoid(np.dot(self.X, self.weights) + self.bias)
            error = np.abs(predictions - self.y)

            # Compute gradients
            gradient_w = np.dot(self.X.T, error) / self.X.shape[0]
            gradient_b = np.sum(error) / self.X.shape[0]

            # Update weights and bias
            self.weights -= self.alpha * gradient_w
            self.bias -= self.alpha * gradient_b
    def weights_and_biases(self):
        return self.weights, self.bias
    def predict(self, arr):
        pred = np.dot(arr, self.weights) + self.bias
        y_pred = sigmoid(pred)
        class_pred = [0 if y<=0.5 else 1 for y in y_pred]
        return class_pred
